%N A219073 Number of n X 3 binary arrays with every 0 a horizontal, diagonal or antidiagonal neighbor to some 1.
%H A219073 R. H. Hardin, <a href="/A219073/b219073.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..210</a>
%H A219073 <a href="/index/Rec#order_07">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (5,11,51,7,27,-33,-3).
%F A219073 Empirical: a(n) = 5*a(n-1) + 11*a(n-2) + 51*a(n-3) + 7*a(n-4) + 27*a(n-5) - 33*a(n-6) - 3*a(n-7).
%F A219073 Empirical g.f.: x*(5 + 22*x + 47*x^2 + 12*x^3 + 15*x^4 - 54*x^5 - 3*x^6) / (1 - 5*x - 11*x^2 - 51*x^3 - 7*x^4 - 27*x^5 + 33*x^6 + 3*x^7). - _Colin Barker_, Jul 25 2018
%F A219073 The above empirical formulas confirmed using the transfer matrix method. - _Andrew Howroyd_, Jul 17 2026
